article.description: — Hyunjung Lee scored a career-high 32 points as Davidson topped Charlotte 75-58 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Lee scores 32 to lift Davidson over Charlotte 75-58
article.linkText: Lee scores 32 to lift Davidson over Charlotte 75-58
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — Hyunjung Lee scored a career-high 32 points as Davidson topped Charlotte 75-58 on Tuesday night. Michael Jones had 18 points for Davidson (5-2), which won its fourth straight game. Aly Khalifa had 18 points for the 49ers (3-3). Jahmir Young added 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
